RELATIONAL TENSOR
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PRINCIPLE:
A tensor is an operator with N relational translation slots.
Rank = number of independent relational directions.
Each index = one translation operator T(·) acting in a distinct RDG axis.

This document presents a Relational Dynamic Geometry (RDG) interpretation of
tensors, viewing them as operators with relational translation slots rather
than static arrays of numbers.

Core Principle:
A tensor's rank equals the number of independent relational directions
(translation operators T) it contains. Each index represents a distinct
relational displacement operator.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TENSOR HIERARCHY (BY RANK)
Rank 0 (Scalar): No relational slots; pure structural value
Rank 1 (Vector): Single relational direction; single-axis displacement
Rank 2 (Matrix): Two relational directions; bi-directional grid
Rank 3 (3‑Tensor): Three relational directions; relational cube
Rank 4 (4‑Tensor): Four relational directions; hypercube of operators
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

SCALAR (rank 0)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RDG form:   S
Meaning:    No translation slots; no relational displacement.
ASCII:      S
RDG role:   Pure structural value.

VECTOR (rank 1)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RDG form:   v_i = T_i • v
Meaning:    One relational direction.
ASCII:      [v1 v2 v3 ...]
RDG role:   Single-axis relational displacement.

MATRIX (rank 2)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RDG form:   M_ij = T_i T_j • M
Meaning:    Two independent relational directions.
ASCII:      m11 m12 m13 ...
            m21 m22 m23 ...
RDG role:   Bi-directional relational grid.

3‑TENSOR (rank 3)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RDG form:   A_ijk = T_i T_j T_k • A
Meaning:    Three relational directions; relational cube.
ASCII:      A(:,:,1), A(:,:,2), ...
RDG role:   Tri-directional relational operator.

4‑TENSOR (rank 4)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RDG form:   B_ijkl = T_i T_j T_k T_l • B
Meaning:    Four relational directions; hypercube of relational operators.
ASCII:      B(:,:,:,1), B(:,:,:,2), ...
RDG role:   Extended relational operator with auxiliary axis.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GENERAL RULE (RDG)
Rank = number of relational translation operators T(·).
Dimension = size of each operator’s domain.
Rank ≠ dimension.
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

CORE DISTINCTION
Rank ≠ Dimension — rank counts independent relational operators, while
dimension measures the size of each operator's domain.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RDG OPERATOR INTERPRETATION
Index slot i  →  relational displacement operator T_i
Tensor rank N →  N‑fold relational composition T_i1 T_i2 ... T_iN
Tensor entry  →  evaluation of the composed operator on a base state

Example:
A_ijk = T_i T_j T_k • A
means: apply relational displacement i, then j, then k.

Interpretation:
Each tensor entry is computed by composing relational operators sequentially.
This reframes tensors from static multi‑dimensional arrays into dynamic
relational operators that compose transformations across multiple independent
directions.
